 ahead of personal obligations? In this comprehensive and stimulating biography Kathryn Tempest delves into contemporary sources to bring to light the personal and political struggles Brutus faced. As the details are revealed—from his own correspondence with Cicero, from the perceptions of his peers, and from the Roman aristocratic values and concepts that held sway in his time—Brutus emerges from legend, revealed to us more surely than ever before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231267423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231267.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles